Package API

Class SwitchDetector

java.lang.Object
API.SwitchDetector
public class SwitchDetector extends Object
A detector that measures changes of the switch position and notifies listeners.
start() must be executed once to start the measurement process.
See start() for details on the measurement process and different listeners.
Use addListener(SwitchListener) to add a SwitchListener.
Author:
Mika Thein

    • start

      public void start()
      Starts the measurement-process. The detector waits PRECISION = 10L milliseconds between each measurement. If any update on the switch position has been detected, all listeners are going to be notified. Currently there are two different scenarios.
      • Single click (SwitchListener.onSingleClick(SwitchEvent)) is triggered whenever any update on the switch position has been detected.
      • Click sequence (SwitchListener.onClickSequence(ArrayList)) is triggered whenever getWaitingTime() milliseconds passed since the last click.
      This method does nothing if isRunning() is true.
      See Also:
      • stop()
      • isRunning()

      public boolean setWaitingTime(long waitingTime)

    • getLatestSwitchEvent

      public SwitchEvent getLatestSwitchEvent()
      Returns the latest switch event. If no switch event has been detected yet, this method will return a SwitchEvent with SwitchEvent.time = 0, SwitchEvent.timeDelta = 0 and SwitchEvent.switchPosition = SwitchEvent.SWITCH_NAN.
      Returns:
      the latest switch event.
